        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ يَقُولُ : \"لاَ يَنْبَغِي لِلرَّجُلِ إِسْلاَفُ اَلسَّمْنِ بِالزَّيْتِ وَ لاَ اَلزَّيْتِ بِالسَّمْنِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3947 - Al-Washsha' narrated from Abdullah ibn Sinan, who said:\nI heard Abu Abdullah (as) say: \"It is not proper for a man to lend ghee in exchange for oil, nor oil in exchange for ghee.\""
        ]
